00:54:33,971 --> 00:54:40,993
I think this was just another example of institutional racism that happens in video games where maybe

1011
00:54:41,373 --> 00:54:46,574
playtesters were testing mostly with white characters, so they never saw that black characters

1012
00:54:46,734 --> 00:54:52,015
are lit really poorly in this game, or need more specular contribution on their reflection

1013
00:54:52,075 --> 00:54:54,056
or light probes or whatever is going on in Skyrim.

1014
00:54:56,439 --> 00:54:58,804
It's important for us to take responsibility for our art,

1015
00:54:59,105 --> 00:55:01,992
and if in doubt, just ask a collaborator

1016
00:55:02,072 --> 00:55:04,197
so that you can kind of avoid situations like these.

1017
00:55:07,119 --> 00:55:12,700
And then the last step is you should maybe iterate on your level, keep trying different

1018
00:55:12,740 --> 00:55:13,521
lighting schemes.

1019
00:55:14,441 --> 00:55:18,982
And this is an example of a sci-fi scene that's lit four different ways.

1020
00:55:19,102 --> 00:55:23,303
So keep experimenting with your lighting, but at the same time, know when to stop and

1021
00:55:23,363 --> 00:55:24,263
move on with your life.

1022
00:55:24,863 --> 00:55:27,744
This is a trap that a lot of level designers fall into.

1023
00:55:27,764 --> 00:55:31,485
They keep tweaking lights a little bit brighter, a little bit darker, as if that'll make a

1024
00:55:31,525 --> 00:55:32,165
huge difference.

1025
00:55:32,285 --> 00:55:32,905
It will not.

1026
00:55:33,385 --> 00:55:33,985
I guarantee you.

1027
00:55:34,025 --> 00:55:36,866
Just make the lights as good as you can.

1028
00:55:37,206 --> 00:55:38,027
And then move on.

1029
00:55:38,047 --> 00:55:39,910
You may come back to it later if you have more time.

1030
00:55:40,090 --> 00:55:41,072
You won't have more time.

1031
00:55:41,172 --> 00:55:43,155
But go back to it later.

1032
00:55:43,675 --> 00:55:44,777
Just say that to yourself.

1033
00:55:45,097 --> 00:55:45,718
And move on.

1034
00:55:45,778 --> 00:55:47,220
And make the rest of your game.

1035
00:55:49,263 --> 00:55:50,164
So to review real quick.

1036
00:55:51,633 --> 00:55:53,214
Lighting sets mood and evokes culture.

1037
00:55:53,434 --> 00:55:57,497
There's four different light types common to a lot of 3D game engines and tool sets.

1038
00:55:58,177 --> 00:56:01,900
Three-point lighting argues that you should think about the task and function of each light

1039
00:56:01,940 --> 00:56:03,861
and what it's doing for the image composition.

1040
00:56:04,882 --> 00:56:05,702
Light globally.

1041
00:56:05,923 --> 00:56:11,126
Do your big lights first and then do start doing spot checks for gameplay and critical path.

1042
00:56:11,767 --> 00:56:16,810
And also know when to stop fiddling with your lights and move on and make your game

1043
00:56:17,030 --> 00:56:18,971
and don't just keep fiddling with one light.

